/** * * Format component stack into pseudo HTML * component stack is an array of strings, e.g.: ['p', 'p', 'Page', ...] * * For html tags mismatch, it will render it for the code block * * ``` * 
 *  {`
 *    
 *       

 *         

 *  `}
 *
* ``` * * For text mismatch, it will render it for the code block * * ``` * 
 * {`
 *   
 *     

 *       "Server Text" (green)
 *       "Client Text" (red)
 *     

 *   
 * `}
 * ```
 *
 * For bad text under a tag it will render it for the code block,
 * e.g. "Mismatched Text" under 

 *
 * ```
 * 
 * {`
 *   
 *     

 *       

 *         "Mismatched Text" (red)
 *      

 *     

 *   
 * `}
 * ```
 *
 */
export declare function PseudoHtmlDiff({ firstContent, secondContent, hydrationMismatchType, reactOutputComponentDiff, ...props }: {
    firstContent: string;
    secondContent: string;
    reactOutputComponentDiff: string;
    hydrationMismatchType: 'tag' | 'text' | 'text-in-tag';
} & React.HTMLAttributes): import("react/jsx-runtime").JSX.Element;
